==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[cock block]]

===Noun===
'''cockblock'''

# {{slang}} A companion who deliberately or inadvertently prevents an aspiring male from having sex with their companion.
#: ''I wanted to take this girl to my room, but her roommate was being too much of a '''cockblock'''.''
{{seeCites}}

===Verb===
'''to cockblock''', past and past participle '''cockblocked''' or '''cockblock'd'''

# {{slang}} An action that prevents a man's pre meditated course of action of romancing a woman. Although it's definition implies sexual behaviour, it is used by various people to portray a man as having sexual intentions which were denied. Some one who acts as the "cockblock" is a "cockblocker", although no actual penis stopping may have taken place. This is because the word has evolved to fit many situations, sexual and non-sexual.
#: ''I knew my roommate wanted to hook up with this dude, but I knew who he was and I had to '''cockblock''' him.''
{{seeCites}}

